{"_id":"ODM1YjRhZWYxOWYy","name":"Mace of Disruption","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"OGVmYWE2MTQ5YTYw","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":19,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":190000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h4>Mace of Disruption</h4><em>Weapon (mace), rare (requires attunement)</em><br><br>\tWhen you hit a fiend or an undead with this magic weapon, that creature takes an extra 2d6 radiant damage. If the target has 25 hit points or fewer after taking this damage, it must succeed on a DC 15 Wisdom saving throw or be destroyed. On a successful save, the creature becomes frightened of you until the end of your next turn.<br><br>While you hold this weapon, it sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet.<br><br>","img":"worlds/toa/journal/magic-items/mace-of-disruption/avatar.webp"}
{"_id":"ODNmN2RmYjI4NGU5","name":"Necklace of Fireballs","content":"<h4>Necklace of Fireballs</h4><em>Wondrous item, rare</em><br /><br />This necklace has 1d6 + 3 beads hanging from it. You can use an action to detach a bead and throw it up to 60 feet away. When it reaches the end of its trajectory, the bead detonates as a 3rd-level fireball spell (save DC 15).<br /><br />You can hurl multiple beads, or even the whole necklace, as one action. When you do so, increase the level of the fireball by 1 for each bead beyond the first.<br />\n<section class=\"secret\"><strong>Tomb of Annihilation Only:</strong><br />This necklace, if found in area S53, has 8 beads. @Actor[N2JkZTE2MGEwNTY2]{Acererak} placed a curse on the necklace, which can be revealed by an <em>identify</em> spell.<br /><br />When any creature dons the cursed necklace, all its beads detonate at once. Each creature in a 20-foot-radius sphere centered on the exploding necklace must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking 56 (16d6) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The wearer of the necklace fails the saving throw automatically. A <em>remove curse</em> spell or similar magic removes the curse from the necklace.</section>","img":"worlds/toa/journal/magic-items/necklace-of-fireballs/avatar.webp","folder":"OGVmYWE2MTQ5YTYw","sort":260000,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":26,"handout-archived":false}}}
