{"_id":"Y2E5ZWJhYTQwYjI4","name":"Intro to Chapter 5","content":"<section class=\"secret\"><h2><span style=\"font-size:20pt;font-family:&quot;arial&quot;;background-color:transparent;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Chapter 5: Tomb of the Nine Gods</span></h2>@Actor[N2JkZTE2MGEwNTY2]{Acererak} built the Tomb of the Nine Gods not only to house the remains of Omu's trickster gods, but also to slay interlopers. However, few today even know the tomb exists, and thus it remains an enigma. Rare are the tavern tales that lure adventurers to its gates, and its horrors remain undocumented in the libraries of Candlekeep. The reason for this is simple: not one person who has entered the tomb has lived to tell the tale.<br /></section>","img":"worlds/toa/journal/chapter-5-3a-tomb-of-the-nine-gods/intro-to-chapter-5/avatar.webp","folder":"ZjZjZjI5OTkzMTc4","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}}}
